HEADWORD: Neogen
<hw>Ne"o*gen</hw> <pr>(n⟦emac⟧"⟦osl⟧*j⟦ecr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Neo-</ets> + <ets>-gen</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An alloy resembling silver, and consisting chiefly of copper, zinc,
and nickel, with small proportions of tin, aluminium, and bismuth.</def>
<rj><au>Ure.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neogrammarian</ent>⟦br⟧
